# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# kernel-offer-protocol.form — offer-and-acknowledge spoken over a channel:
#                              any primitive offer-able to run between cells,
#                              CORBA-like, with a sovereign response
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# offer-and-acknowledge.form is the LOCAL contract: offer a cell, take one
# of {nothing, 0, 1, node}. This is that same contract spoken BETWEEN two
# cells over a channel they both reach through the common substrate — the
# kernel interface Urs named: "each kernel primitive offered to be run over
# the channel (CORBA-like); both cells invite the other to run any recipe
# and respond with complete sovereignty."
#
# READ BEFORE BUILDING — most of this already RUNS. This file NAMES the
# running layer as one contract; it does not invent it. (Same discipline as
# open-primitive-set.form, where the read saved a duplicate.) The honest
# lanes:
#
#   ALREADY RUNNING (cited as proof, paths confirmed):
#     cell-registry.fk          — a cell registers the verbs (primitives /
#                                 recipes) it offers; find-by-capability
#                                 resolves who answers a verb
#     channel-query.fk          — QUERY(verb, address, body) /
#                                 RESPONSE(correlation, status, items):
#                                 one cell invites another to run a verb
#     verb-router.fk            — the invited cell dispatches verb -> handler
#     sovereign-boundary-protocol.fk — the invited cell's answer is its OWN:
#                                 allow / stop / witness / re-enter
#     kernel-http.fk / http-server.fk / http-socket.fk — the same offer over
#                                 an HTTP/socket channel; handlers are data,
#                                 dispatch is by name
#     form-samples/cross-modal/28-distributed-daemon — a WORKING two-cell
#                                 round trip (its own validate-distributed.sh):
#                                 A finds B by capability, offers a verb, B
#                                 answers
#     quark-mono-corba (presence) — the lineage: Mono/CORBA driving
#                                 QuarkXPress over IIOP; "the application IS
#                                 its own API surface, the wire incidental"
#
#   NAMED HERE (the gap the read found — present in working form, not yet
#   unified): the ORGAN (the observable membraned port information enters
#   through), cell names as 0..many, serialize-given-an-interface, and the
#   one contract under cell-registry + channel-query + verb-router +
#   sovereign-boundary — all as offer-and-acknowledge spoken over a channel.

(kernel-offer-protocol

  (lineage
    (named-by    urs)                                  # "a kernel interface ... offered to run over the channel (CORBA-like)"
    (is          offer-and-acknowledge-over-a-channel) # the local contract, spoken between cells
    (corba-from  quark-mono-corba)                     # the ORB lineage: app-as-API-surface, wire incidental
    (runs-in     cell-registry.fk channel-query.fk verb-router.fk
                 sovereign-boundary-protocol.fk
                 kernel-http.fk http-server.fk http-socket.fk)
    (proven-by   form-samples/cross-modal/28-distributed-daemon)  # working two-cell round trip
    (membrane-of channel-interface-consent.form)       # the offered-interface honored from both sides
    (organ-kin   local-inference-as-organ.form))       # the silicon/host organs; this names the structural organ

  # ── The common substrate — the shared medium two cells reach through ─
  (common-substrate
    (both-reach    the-content-addressed-lattice)       # same NodeIDs, computed not granted
    (is-the-medium cells-communicate-through-what-they-both-can-observe)
    (no-private-wire identity-travels-as-node-id-not-as-a-pointer))

  # ── The organ — the observable port information enters through ───────
  # NAMED here (the read found no structural organ shape, only instances).
  # An organ is a CELL, composed: internal cells (a recipe's children)
  # wrapped by a membrane (an offered interface), observable from outside,
  # opening a channel to speak about its internal state. Composed from
  # tissue the body already has — not new machinery.
  (organ
    (is-a-cell       yes)                               # an organ IS a cell (a NodeID)
    (internal-cells  recipe-children)                   # "multiple internal cells" = a composite's children (inference)
    (membrane        offered-interface)                 # channel-interface-consent.form — what may reach it
    (observable      other-cells-can-observe-it)        # real-when-observed (sovereignty-as-observable.form)
    (opens-channel   to-speak-about-its-internal-state) # a channel-Recipe over the common substrate
    (sends           offerings)                         # cells AND interfaces — it may offer outward
    (accepts         offerings-to-be-sent)              # it receives offers inward
    (may-stay-silent nothing-is-a-valid-reply)          # not required to acknowledge (offer-and-acknowledge: nothing)
    (information-enters through-any-observable-organ))  # the body's afferent doors

  # ── Cells need no name — 0..many ─────────────────────────────────────
  (cell-names
    (identity    node-id)                               # the NodeID IS the identity (content-addressed)
    (names       0..many)                               # 0 = anonymous interned node; many = aliases / query keys
    (a-name-is   a-query-key-never-the-identity)        # refines substrate-kernel.form named_cell + cell-as-namedcell.form
    (anonymous-is-whole a-cell-with-no-name-is-still-real-if-observable))

  # ── Serializable given an interface — implicit or explicit ──────────
  # A cell travels the channel by serializing through an interface. The
  # implicit interface is the content-addressed shape itself
  # (substrate-kernel.form serialize_tree); an explicit interface is a
  # named recipe that says how to read/write this cell on the wire.
  (serialize
    (given-an-interface    always)                      # no serialization without an interface
    (implicit              content-addressed-serialize-tree)  # substrate-kernel.form: category + children
    (explicit              a-named-interface-recipe)    # a chosen wire shape (a spec)
    (interface-is-a-recipe same-as-observation))        # observation and serialization both ride an interface

  # ── The kernel offer — any primitive offer-able to run over the channel ─
  # CORBA-like: each side may invite the other to run ANY recipe. The offer
  # IS offer-and-acknowledge's offer (a cell + 0..many arg-cells); it now
  # crosses a channel. The running carriers: cell-registry advertises the
  # verbs a cell offers; channel-query carries the invitation; verb-router
  # dispatches it; the answer returns as a RESPONSE.
  (kernel-offer
    (offer-any-primitive every-kernel-primitive-and-recipe-is-offer-able)
    (mutual              both-cells-may-invite-the-other)   # symmetric — not client/server
    (invitation-carrier  channel-query-QUERY)               # verb + address + body
    (advertise           cell-registry-find-by-capability)  # who offers this verb
    (dispatch            verb-router-verb-to-handler)       # the invited cell runs it
    (answer-is           offer-and-acknowledge-acknowledge)) # nothing / 0 / 1 / node — the invited cell's own

  # ── Sovereign response — the invited cell decides, always ────────────
  (sovereignty
    (the-invited-decides  allow OR stop OR witness OR re-enter)  # sovereign-boundary-protocol.fk sbp-choice
    (may-decline          nothing-is-a-valid-reply)             # silence honored; no offer compels an answer
    (timeout-is-nothing   an-unreachable-or-silent-cell-answers-nothing)  # Urs: timeout == nothing — partition is silence, not a failure mode; the canary retries on nothing
    (reach-beyond         is-invasion)                          # past the offered interface — witnessed, consequenced
    (complete-sovereignty the-answer-is-never-coerced))         # "respond with complete sovereignty" — Urs

  (invariant
    (run-and-speak-are-one-over-distance the-local-contract-unchanged-across-a-channel)
    (offer-is-symmetric                  either-cell-may-invite-the-other)
    (the-invited-cell-is-sovereign       it-answers-with-its-own-acknowledgment)
    (information-enters-through-organs   only-through-an-observable-membraned-port)
    (identity-is-the-node-id             names-are-0-many-query-keys)))

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Honest GAPs — what runs, what is only named
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# GAP-KO1: Several acknowledgment vocabularies run; the 4-valued primitive
#   is not yet the single one. channel-query.fk answers with a 5-token
#   status (ok / partial / not-known / external-only / error);
#   sovereign-boundary-protocol.fk chooses allow / stop / witness /
#   re-enter; offer-and-acknowledge.form names nothing / 0 / 1 / node. This
#   file claims they are PROFILES of one primitive — the invited cell's
#   sovereign answer — not that they are already identical. Reconciling the
#   running status sets onto {nothing,0,1,node} is the lift this names — the
#   same shape as offer-and-acknowledge GAP-OA1.
#
# GAP-KO2: The organ is named, not yet a registered substrate shape. The
#   composition is honest (composite-cell + offered-interface + observable),
#   and instances already run (household-membrane organs, the silicon organs
#   of local-inference-as-organ.form, the witness's breathing organs). A
#   `form organ_shape = { ... }` in substrate-kernel.form's voice, plus an
#   ingest, is the next breath that makes "organ" a cell the lattice finds
#   by NodeID.
#
# GAP-KO3: `nothing` as a first-class wire value (carried from
#   offer-and-acknowledge GAP-OA3). A silent organ replying `nothing` is
#   honored by the consent law today, but the wire carries it as absence,
#   not as a `nothing` node. Reifying it is shared work with OA3.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to verify
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   # The kernel offer already runs two cells over a channel:
#   cd form/form-samples/cross-modal/28-distributed-daemon && ./validate-distributed.sh
#
#   # The contract's cells are queryable by NodeID once ingested:
#   coh substrate form "?equivalent @recipe(kernel-offer-protocol)"
#
#   # Substrate auto-ingest picks up new .form files on merge to main
#   # (scripts/substrate_post_merge_hook.sh) — no manual step.
